    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-06-29T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-06-29T15:00:00-05:00" n="511"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d511">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">394.1153 Smith Company, Werner G./18:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lockhart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-06-29T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 29, 1938—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>408. Following for Tokyo: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“220 June 29, 4 p.m. Your 391, June 20, 4 p.m.,<note n="95"
                                xml:id="d511fn95">See telegram No. 873, June 20, 7 p.m., from the
                                Consul General at Shanghai, <ref target="#pg_367">p.
                                367</ref>.</note> and Nanking’s 127, June 27, 4 p.m.<note n="96"
                                xml:id="d511fn96">Not printed.</note> (which Shanghai has been
                            requested to repeat to you) in regard to wood oil of Werner G.
                            Smith.</p>
                        <pb facs="0389" n="385" xml:id="pg_385"/>
                        <p>The Department desires that, in such manner as you deem appropriate, you
                            ask the Foreign Office whether any reports of the investigation promised
                            have been received and express your Government’s increasing concern over
                            the continued delay in the release of the wood oil.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Please repeat to Tokyo Nanking’s 127, June 27, 4 p.m., and inform Nanking of
                    action taken.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
